---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | LeavingAmerica.co"
  description="Cookie Policy for LeavingAmerica.co. Learn how we use cookies and how to manage them."
>
<div class="ip-page">

  <div class="ip-header">
    <div class="ip-wrap">
      <span class="ip-label">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="ip-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="ip-lead">This Cookie Policy explains how LeavingAmerica.co uses cookies and similar tracking technologies when you visit our website.</p>
      <p class="ip-date">Last updated: June 17, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ip-body">
    <div class="ip-wrap">

<h2>What Are Cookies</h2>
<p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and to provide information to website owners.</p>

<h2>Cookies We Use</h2>

<h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
<p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They enable core functionality such as storing your tool inputs and session preferences temporarily in your browser. These cookies are required for core website functionality and cannot be disabled through our cookie preferences.</p>

<h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
<p>We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors interact with our website. Google Analytics uses cookies to collect information such as how many people visit our site, which pages they visit, and how long they stay. This information is used in aggregated form to help us understand how visitors use the website. You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>

<h3>Advertising Cookies</h3>
<p>We display advertisements through Google AdSense. Google uses cookies to show you relevant ads based on your interests and previous browsing activity. You can manage your Google ad preferences at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank">Google Ad Settings</a>.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Cookies</h2>
<p>Some cookies on our website are set by third-party services. We do not control these cookies. The third parties that may set cookies on our website include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Google Analytics</li>
<li>Google AdSense</li>
<li>Affiliate partner tracking systems used to measure referrals and commissions</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Control Cookies</h2>
<p>You can control and manage cookies in several ways:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Browser settings:</strong> Most browsers allow you to refuse or delete cookies. Refer to your browser's help documentation for instructions.</li>
<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">opt-out browser add-on</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Google Ads:</strong> Manage preferences at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank">adssettings.google.com</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of our website.</p>
<p>Where required by law, visitors may be presented with a cookie consent banner allowing them to manage non-essential cookies before they are set.</p>

<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. We will notify you of changes by updating the date at the top of this page.</p>

<h2>Contact</h2>
<p>For questions about our use of cookies, contact us at:<br>
<a href="mailto:contact@leavingamerica.co">contact@leavingamerica.co</a></p>

    </div>
  </div>

</div>
</BaseLayout>
